// ── Phase 05.1-05 smoke-test bug-fix regression — Bug 1 ──
// `Eg vil skrive på nynorsk` — `skrive` IS the infinitive of å skrive. The
// rule was firing with fix="skrive ut" because the NN vocab-seam's
// verbInfinitive map overwrites `skrive → <phrasal-verb baseWord>` across
// skrive_av / skrive_opp / skrive_ut (all share perfektum_partisipp="skrive").
// Self-mapping guard (`inf !== w`) skipped skrive_verb's own row but not
// the phrasal-verb siblings' rows. Fix: rule now short-circuits when
// `validWords.has('å ' + word)` — the seam emits `å skrive` via
// conjugations.presens.former.infinitiv for every verb entry, so a true
// bare infinitive is always detectable by the "å X is valid" presence.
{"id":"nn-modal-false-pos-skrive-001","text":"Eg vil skrive på nynorsk","expected":[],"must_not_flag":[]}
